---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="What Certifications Do I Need for Importing Plant Extracts? | Complete Guide"
  description="Complete guide to required certifications for importing plant extracts, herbal extracts, and natural ingredients to different countries: US, EU, Canada, Australia, and more."
>
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem)] font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">What Certifications Do I Need for Importing Plant Extracts?</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg">A complete guide for importers, distributors, and manufacturers importing plant extracts and natural ingredients from China to global markets.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">General Certifications Required for All Markets</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">These are the basic certifications you will need for importing plant extracts to almost any country:
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-3 space-y-3">
            <li>
              <strong>Certificate of Analysis (COA)</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-1">Issued by the manufacturer, this document shows the test results for each batch of product, including purity, active ingredient content, heavy metal levels, microbial limits, and other quality parameters. Customs officials in most countries require a COA to verify product quality.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Safety Data Sheet (SDS/MSDS)</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-1">This document provides information about the product's properties, hazards, handling, storage, and emergency measures. Required for international shipping and customs clearance.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Technical Data Sheet (TDS)</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-1">Contains detailed technical information about the product, including specifications, applications, and storage conditions. Often required for product registration and regulatory compliance.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Certificate of Origin (CO)</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-1">Issued by the Chamber of Commerce in the exporting country, this document verifies where the product was manufactured. Required for customs clearance and to determine applicable import duties.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Commercial Invoice & Packing List</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-1">Standard shipping documents that show the value, quantity, and description of the goods being shipped.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Specific Requirements by Country/Region</h2>
        
        <div class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">🇺🇸 United States</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">To import plant extracts to the US, you will need:
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-2">
              <li>FDA registration for the manufacturing facility</li>
              <li>GRAS (Generally Recognized as Safe) status for the ingredient (for food and dietary supplement use)</li>
              <li>Dietary Supplement Ingredient New Dietary Ingredient (NDI) notification for new dietary ingredients</li>
              <li>INCI listing for cosmetic ingredients</li>
              <li>Phytosanitary certificate for certain plant products</li>
              <li>DSHEA compliance for dietary supplements</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">🇪🇺 European Union</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">To import plant extracts to the EU, you will need:
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-2">
              <li>REACH (Registration, Evaluation, Authorization and Restriction of Chemicals) registration for the ingredient</li>
              <li>EFSA (European Food Safety Authority) approval for food and supplement ingredients</li>
              <li>Cosing database listing for cosmetic ingredients</li>
              <li>EU GMP (Good Manufacturing Practice) certification</li>
              <li>Phytosanitary certificate for plant products</li>
              <li>Novel Food approval for new ingredients not previously used in the EU</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">🇨🇦 Canada</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm">
              <li>Health Canada Natural Product Number (NPN) for natural health products</li>
              <li>Site GMP certification</li>
              <li>Phytosanitary certificate</li>
              <li>Certificate of Free Sale</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">🇦🇺 Australia</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm">
              <li>TGA (Therapeutic Goods Administration) listing for therapeutic goods</li>
              <li>FSANZ (Food Standards Australia New Zealand) approval for food ingredients</li>
              <li>Phytosanitary certificate</li>
              <li>Import permit from the Department of Agriculture</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">🇯🇵 Japan</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm">
              <li>MHLW (Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare) approval</li>
              <li>JAS certification for agricultural products</li>
              <li>Phytosanitary certificate</li>
              <li>Import notification to the quarantine station</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">🇰🇷 South Korea</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm">
              <li>KFDA (Korea Food and Drug Administration) approval</li>
              <li>Health functional food certification for supplements</li>
              <li>Phytosanitary certificate</li>
              <li>Import license from MFDS</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Certifications for Specific Product Types</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Food & Dietary Supplements</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
              <li>✅ GMP (Good Manufacturing Practice)</li>
              <li>✅ HACCP (Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Points)</li>
              <li>✅ Kosher certification (for Jewish markets)</li>
              <li>✅ Halal certification (for Muslim markets)</li>
              <li>✅ Organic certification (for organic products)</li>
              <li>✅ Non-GMO certification</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Cosmetic Ingredients</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
              <li>✅ ISO 22716 (Cosmetic GMP)</li>
              <li>✅ CPSR (Cosmetic Product Safety Report)</li>
              <li>✅ INCI name listing</li>
              <li>✅ Heavy metal and microbial test reports</li>
              <li>✅ Animal cruelty-free certification (if required)</li>
              <li>✅ Vegan certification (if required)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-green-200 mt-12">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-4">We Provide All Required Certifications for Your Import</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">When you import plant extracts, cosmetic ingredients, or food additives from Weiyijie Bio, we provide all the required certification documents for your market, free of charge. We work with you to ensure smooth customs clearance and regulatory compliance.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✅</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700">All standard documents (COA, SDS, TDS, CO) provided for every order</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✅</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700">Market-specific certifications available (FDA, REACH, Kosher, Halal, Organic, etc.)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✅</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700">We help you prepare all required documentation for customs clearance</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✅</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700">Regulatory support for product registration in your market</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✅</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700">100% refund guarantee if products are detained by customs due to missing documentation</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="text-center">
          <a href="/#contact" class="bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-semibold px-8 py-3 rounded-lg inline-block transition-all">
            Discuss Your Import Requirements
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
